    <h3>The Critical Nature of Communication in AxtCity</h3>
    <div class="section-content">
        <p>For any member or affiliate working with the AxtCity Core Team, **communication and responsiveness are the absolute minimum requirements.** Our community's foundation is built on coordinated effort and mutual reliability. When an individual entirely ceases communication, it effectively halts processes and destabilizes the team.</p>
        
        <p style="margin-top: 15px;">**Explanation of Impact:**</p>
        <p>A non-responsive member is functionally equivalent to an absent member, creating immediate negative impacts:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>**Operational Blockage:** If the user held any specific role (even a minor one), the lack of response prevents handoffs, knowledge transfer, and continuation of ongoing tasks.</li>
            <li>**Resource Waste:** Time and effort spent by active team members attempting to contact, coordinate, or compensate for the non-responsive individual are wasted resources.</li>
            <li>**Integrity Breach:** Active participation and communication are tenets of respect for the project and fellow team members. Chronic non-responsiveness represents a serious breach of trust and commitment.</li>
        </ul>
        <p style="margin-top: 15px;">This failure to maintain basic responsiveness demonstrates an irreconcilable detachment from the project's integrity, necessitating this final and permanent administrative action.</p>
